Compute Instance Agent exposes
GetInstanceAgentPlugin and
ListInstanceAgentPlugins only in the pinned SDK,
so the published runtime is bind-existing and
observe-only.
Bind identity is explicit: reconcile requires
compartmentId, instanceagentId, and pluginName,
tracks the composite identity in status, and
uses ListInstanceAgentPlugins only to confirm
absence after a reread no longer finds the
tracked plugin.
No OCI create, update, or delete operation is
published. Plugin enable or disable remains part
of Core UpdateInstance and is out of scope for
this package.
Visible plugin states RUNNING, STOPPED,
NOT_SUPPORTED, and INVALID are all stable
observed states. Delete is Kubernetes-local
unbind only and settles through best-effort
local cleanup rather than cloud-side terminal
waiting.
end note
